summary: This is an email chain between FBI personnel and Assistant U.S. Attorneys from the Southern District of New York regarding the shipment of approximately 23 boxes of case records from two FBI case files (72-MM-113327 and 31E-MM-108062) for an investigation. It shows coordination between law enforcement and prosecutors.

events.title: Prosecutors provide contact info and discuss case records
events.description: Assistant U.S. Attorneys from SDNY email FBI personnel to provide their contact information and confirm details about approximately 23 boxes of case records from two FBI case files to be shipped for their investigation.

events.title: FBI confirms shipment of case record boxes
events.description: FBI personnel confirm that the boxes of case records will be shipped via FedEx in the afternoon.

keyFacts: The document is an email chain dated June 27-28, 2019, regarding the transfer of case records for an investigation.
Approximately 23 boxes of papers were to be shipped, containing records from FBI case files 72-MM-113327 and 31E-MM-108062.
The correspondence is between FBI personnel and Assistant U.S. Attorneys from the Southern District of New York, who are prosecutors working on the investigation.
The email shows logistical coordination for evidence transfer between law enforcement and prosecutors.
